This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring May 1, 2013, as Loyalty Day in the United States. Loyalty Day is a day to recognize the American spirit of loyalty and the sacrifices made for the nation. The proclamation encourages citizens to reaffirm their allegiance to the United States, its Constitution, and its founding values. It also calls upon people to support this national observance by displaying the flag of the United States or pledging allegiance to the Republic. The proclamation emphasizes the enduring task of working towards lasting freedom and true equality for all Americans.